This is another debate: do we need an else clause if it will say: `else None`. Do we even need `None` when we can drop the else clause.

My stance on this is: Explicit is better than Implicit. Especially if WDL aims to be human-readable. As you simply can not read things that are implicit. So I would favour having `else None` over not having it at all. Optionals are something that takes some time to get yourself adjusted to if you have not seen them before. If WDL becomes riddled with implicits concerning optionals I fear that it will become much less accessible.

