The above would produce `path $`, and single `$`  usually indicates an illegal JSON object (occurs when accessing secured resources that produce HTML documents as HTTP 403, exactly the same as you mentioned).

As far as I understand how Gson `JsonReader` works, it only consumes an internal buffer filled up from the `Reader` (1K?) to determine the next JSON token by character not reading entire string, and exposing the current buffer state is probably not a good idea as well as reading the next token entirely (strings can be expensive to collect/read and concatenate/propagate via exception messages; buffer current position can be close to the very end of the buffer therefore emitting a very short string if not reading the next data to the buffer; reading the next data may fail; etc).

A possible work-around for your Gson version:

```java
final class TrackingReader
		extends Reader {

	private final Reader reader;

	private char[] buffer;

	TrackingReader(final Reader reader) {
		this.reader = reader;
	}

	@Override
	public int read(@NotNull final char[] buffer, final int offset, final int length)
			throws IOException {
		final int read = reader.read(buffer, offset, length);
		this.buffer = new char[read];
		System.arraycopy(buffer, offset, this.buffer, 0, read);
		return read;
	}

	@Override
	public void close()
			throws IOException {
		reader.close();
	}

	String getBufferAsString() {
		return new String(buffer);
	}

}
```

```java
final class TrackingJsonReader
		extends JsonReader {

	private final TrackingReader trackingReader;

	private TrackingJsonReader(final TrackingReader trackingReader) {
		super(trackingReader);
		this.trackingReader = trackingReader;
	}

	static JsonReader get(final TrackingReader trackingReader) {
		return new TrackingJsonReader(trackingReader);
	}

	@Override
	public void beginObject()
			throws IOException {
		try {
			super.beginObject();
		} catch ( final IllegalStateException ex ) {
			if ( isRoot() ) {
				throw new IllegalArgumentException(readStatus());
			}
			throw ex;
		}
	}

	private boolean isRoot() {
		return getPath().equals("$");
	}

	private String readStatus()
			throws IOException {
		final Appendable builder = new StringBuilder();
		builder.append("VALUE: `");
		switch ( peek() ) {
		case STRING:
			// Reading the next string may be too expensive, but we are fine with it here
			builder.append(nextString());
			break;
		default:
			throw new UnsupportedOperationException("TODO");
		}
		builder.append("`  BUFFER: `");
		builder.append(trackingReader.getBufferAsString());
		builder.append("`");
		return builder.toString();
	}

}
