Yeah, that was what I thought initially too, but then @blickly  pointed out that the [compiler (correctly) complains about the type mismatch in this example](https://closure-compiler.appspot.com/home#code%3D%252F%252F%2520%253D%253DClosureCompiler%253D%253D%250A%252F%252F%2520%2540compilation_level%2520ADVANCED_OPTIMIZATIONS%250A%252F%252F%2520%2540output_file_name%2520default.js%250A%252F%252F%2520%253D%253D%252FClosureCompiler%253D%253D%250A%250A%252F%252F%2520ADD%2520YOUR%2520CODE%2520HERE%250A%250A%252F**%250A%2520*%2520%2540constructor%250A%2520*%252F%250Afunction%2520Foo()%2520%257B%250A%2520%2520this.bar%2520%253D%252042%253B%250A%257D%250A%250A%252F**%250A%2520*%2520%2540typedef%2520%257Bfunction(this%253A%2520Foo)%257D%250A%2520*%252F%250AFoo.funcType%253B%250A%250A%252F**%2520%2540const%2520%257BObject%253Cstring%252C%2520Foo.funcType%253E%257D%2520*%252F%250Avar%2520funcs%2520%253D%2520%257B%257D%253B%250A%250A%252F**%2520%2540type%2520%257BFoo.funcType%257D%2520*%252F%250Afuncs%255B'baz'%255D%2520%253D%2520function%2520()%2520%257B%250A%2520%2520%2520var%2520%252F**%2520string%2520*%252F%2520s%2520%253D%2520this.bar%253B%250A%257D%250A):

```JS
/**
 * @constructor
 */
function Foo() {
  this.bar = 42;
}

/**
 * @typedef {function(this: Foo)}
 */
Foo.funcType;

/** @const {Object<string, Foo.funcType>} */
var funcs = {};

/** @type {Foo.funcType} */
funcs['baz'] = function () {
   var /** string */ s = this.bar;
}
```

```
JSC_TYPE_MISMATCH: initializing variable
found   : number
required: string at line 20 character 25
   var /** string */ s = this.bar;
                         ^
```
…so it's definitely looking into the typedef for *some* of the types.

